WEBVTT

00:00.756 --> 00:02.622
Narrator: PREVIOUSLY ON
"THE HAVES AND THE HAVE NOTS"...

00:02.622 --> 00:04.135
YOU PRAY FOR ME.
I WILL.

00:04.135 --> 00:07.173
HERE IT GOES.
TALK TO ME, BOY!

00:07.173 --> 00:08.341
Wyatt: SHE'S NOT LEAVING,
JEFFREY.

00:08.341 --> 00:10.476
YES, SHE IS, WYATT.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

00:10.476 --> 00:12.378
UM, MAYBE THIS WASN'T
A GOOD IDEA.

00:12.378 --> 00:15.549
MOM, WYATT IS NOT
FOLLOWING THE RULES!

00:15.549 --> 00:16.683
GET OUT!

00:16.683 --> 00:20.120
ARE YOU ASKING ME
TO TAMPER WITH THE EVIDENCE?

00:20.120 --> 00:22.222
I'M NOT ASKING YOU
ANYTHING.

00:22.222 --> 00:23.289
IF IT'S NOT YOU

00:23.289 --> 00:25.559
THAT'S SLEEPING
WITH THIS WHORE...

00:25.559 --> 00:30.196
THEN IT HAS TO BE YOU,
JIM.

00:48.048 --> 00:49.716
ANYBODY?

00:55.455 --> 00:59.893
VERONICA,
WE NEED TO SPEAK IN PRIVATE.

00:59.893 --> 01:03.704
NO.
ENOUGH WITH THE PRIVACY.

01:03.704 --> 01:05.105
I WANT ANSWERS, DAVID.

01:13.747 --> 01:18.519
[ LAUGHS ] OKAY.

01:18.519 --> 01:22.556
YOU ALL STAND HERE
LIKE THE CAT GOT YOUR TONGUE.

01:26.627 --> 01:29.596
JIM,
DETECTIVE RANKINS,

01:29.596 --> 01:33.867
WOULD YOU BE SO KIND AS TO
GIVE ME AND MY WIFE A MOMENT?

01:38.271 --> 01:39.806
SURE.

01:39.806 --> 01:43.109
I'M HEADED TO YOUR BOSS NEXT,
DETECTIVE,

01:43.109 --> 01:44.377
IF I DON'T GET
SOME ANSWERS.

01:44.377 --> 01:45.378
VERONICA...

01:45.378 --> 01:48.782
WHAT?
...LET THE MAN GO.

02:00.493 --> 02:04.470
I DON'T ENJOY
BEING MADE A FOOL OF.

02:04.470 --> 02:07.974
HONEY, NO ONE'S TRYING
TO MAKE A FOOL OUT OF YOU.

02:07.974 --> 02:10.076
THEN TELL ME
WHAT'S GOING ON.

02:10.076 --> 02:11.477
I WANT TO.

02:11.477 --> 02:13.647
THEN DO IT!

02:13.647 --> 02:16.583
IT'S TOO COMPLICATED.
OH, DAVID, PLEASE.

02:16.583 --> 02:19.052
I'M TRYING
TO PROTECT YOU.

02:19.052 --> 02:20.887
FROM WHAT?!

02:20.887 --> 02:25.258
IF I TOLD YOU, YOU WOULD
NO LONGER BE PROTECTED.

02:28.529 --> 02:30.330
HOW DEEP ARE YOU
IN THIS?

02:30.330 --> 02:32.465
VERONICA ‐‐
SPEAK!

02:32.465 --> 02:35.468
I WILL NOT
LET YOU IN ON THIS!

02:38.404 --> 02:41.074
YOU ARE MY HUSBAND.
[ SIGHS ]

02:41.074 --> 02:43.243
IF YOU'RE IN IT,
I'M ALREADY INVOLVED.

02:43.243 --> 02:47.013
THIS WHOLE THING
IS TOO UGLY.

02:47.013 --> 02:51.752
DAVID, I'M LISTENING.

02:51.752 --> 02:56.356
ALL I CAN TELL YOU
IS WHAT I'VE TOLD YOU BEFORE.

02:56.356 --> 02:59.292
WHAT WAS THAT?

02:59.292 --> 03:04.204
I AM
REPRESENTING A CLIENT.

03:04.204 --> 03:06.840
I'M TRYING TO SOLVE
A VERY COMPLEX

03:06.840 --> 03:09.275
AND DIFFICULT SITUATION
WITH THAT WOMAN.

03:09.275 --> 03:10.711
CANDACE?

03:10.711 --> 03:13.880
YES.

03:13.880 --> 03:16.883
‐‐Captions by VITAC‐‐
www.vitac.com

03:16.883 --> 03:19.886
CAPTIONS PAID FOR BY
DISCOVERY COMMUNICATIONS

03:24.625 --> 03:25.726
CANDACE?

03:25.726 --> 03:28.094
YES.

03:28.094 --> 03:31.497
IS IT JIM?

03:33.600 --> 03:36.136
NO. IT'S A CLIENT.

03:36.136 --> 03:38.104
ARE YOU SURE?

03:38.104 --> 03:41.407
YES.

03:41.407 --> 03:42.643
THEN WHO IS IT?

03:42.643 --> 03:46.547
I CAN'T TELL YOU,
ESPECIALLY NOW.

03:46.547 --> 03:49.583
IT ‐‐ IT'S BEST
IF YOU DON'T KNOW.

03:49.583 --> 03:51.952
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:51.952 --> 03:54.487
ANOTHER THING I DON'T LIKE,
DAVID ‐‐

03:54.487 --> 03:57.023
BEING KEPT IN THE DARK.

03:57.023 --> 03:59.860
SWEETHEART, I KNOW THAT.

03:59.860 --> 04:01.868
BUT THIS IS
HOW IT HAS TO BE.

04:01.868 --> 04:04.971
SO THAT BOY
IS SITTING IN JAIL,

04:04.971 --> 04:09.710
AND YOU KNOW SOMETHING,
AND YOU CAN'T TELL ME?

04:09.710 --> 04:10.777
NO, I CANNOT.

04:10.777 --> 04:11.945
IS HE INNOCENT?

04:11.945 --> 04:15.582
INNOCENT?

04:15.582 --> 04:18.652
I DON'T ‐‐ I DON'T KNOW
ANYTHING ABOUT THAT.

04:18.652 --> 04:21.988
WELL, YOU SEEMED TO KNOW
A LOT ABOUT IT UP UNTIL TODAY.

04:21.988 --> 04:24.825
VERONICA, LET IT GO.

04:24.825 --> 04:28.929
NO.

04:34.501 --> 04:36.870
NO.

04:36.870 --> 04:40.040
PLEASE.
NO!

04:40.040 --> 04:41.742
NOT UNTIL I FIND OUT
WHAT'S GOING ON.

04:41.742 --> 04:45.345
NOW, YOU CAN EITHER TELL ME
OR I CAN FIND OUT ON MY OWN.

04:45.345 --> 04:46.780
BUT IF I DO
ALL THIS WORK

04:46.780 --> 04:48.682
TO FIND OUT
YOU'RE INVOLVED IN IT...

04:51.151 --> 04:54.020
DAVID...

04:54.020 --> 04:56.422
IT WILL BE HELL TO PAY.

05:09.843 --> 05:10.977
HEY, THERE.

05:10.977 --> 05:12.078
Wyatt: HI.

05:12.078 --> 05:13.714
YOU BROUGHT FLOWERS?

05:13.714 --> 05:16.116
YES.

05:16.116 --> 05:18.118
WELL,
THANKS, JEFFREY.

05:18.118 --> 05:20.854
NO, NO, NO.
HE PICKED THEM HIMSELF.

05:20.854 --> 05:22.022
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

05:22.022 --> 05:24.858
OH, WELL, THANK YOU.

05:24.858 --> 05:26.527
SO,
YOU GO HOME TODAY?

05:26.527 --> 05:29.563
YEAH.
MY DAD'S PICKING ME UP LATER.

05:29.563 --> 05:30.664
OKAY. GOOD FOR YOU.

05:33.399 --> 05:34.935
UM, WHERE'S MOM?

05:34.935 --> 05:37.704
STILL ON VACATION.

05:37.704 --> 05:40.206
OH. OKAY.

05:40.206 --> 05:43.276
WELL, I'M SURE IF SHE KNEW,
SHE WOULD HAVE BEEN HERE.

05:43.276 --> 05:44.444
I KNOW.

05:44.444 --> 05:46.346
LET'S HOPE.

05:46.346 --> 05:47.748
SHE WOULD HAVE,
WYATT.

05:47.748 --> 05:49.315
IF YOU SAY SO.

05:52.385 --> 05:54.888
HOW ARE YOU, AMANDA?

05:54.888 --> 05:57.290
I'M FINE.
GOOD.

05:57.290 --> 05:59.693
YOU KNOW, WE ALL THINK THAT
WHEN SOMETHING LIKE THIS OCCURS,

05:59.693 --> 06:01.134
IT'S USUALLY ‐‐

06:01.134 --> 06:03.336
DON'T, JEFFREY.
JUST DON'T.

06:03.336 --> 06:05.639
YEAH. DON'T.

06:05.639 --> 06:06.907
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

06:06.907 --> 06:08.074
I JUST THINK THAT

06:08.074 --> 06:09.510
THERE IS A LOT OF THINGS
THAT NEED TO BE SAID,

06:09.510 --> 06:11.945
AND IT'S NOT HEALTHY TO LEAVE IT
JUST FLOATING IN THE AIR.

06:11.945 --> 06:13.213
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:13.213 --> 06:15.115
YOU'RE
SUCH A HYPOCRITE.

06:15.115 --> 06:18.018
AND HOW IS THAT, WYATT?

06:18.018 --> 06:20.420
I CAN'T DEAL WITH
ANY OF THE FIGHTING.

06:20.420 --> 06:21.622
YEAH, BUT HE SAID ‐‐

06:21.622 --> 06:22.823
I CAN'T.

06:22.823 --> 06:24.891
SORRY.

06:27.293 --> 06:29.262
YOU LOOK GOOD,
WYATT.

06:29.262 --> 06:31.264
DO I?
YEAH.

06:31.264 --> 06:34.935
YOU SEEM HAPPY IN YOUR OWN
CURMUDGING KIND OF WAY.

06:34.935 --> 06:37.938
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHAT'S GOING ON?

06:37.938 --> 06:41.007
DO YOU REMEMBER LAURA?
YEAH.

06:41.007 --> 06:43.644
WE'RE BACK ON.
WHAT?

06:43.644 --> 06:45.278
MM‐HMM. YEAH.

06:45.278 --> 06:46.947
I RAN INTO HER
THE OTHER DAY.

06:46.947 --> 06:48.214
WE'VE BEEN TALKING
NONSTOP.

06:48.214 --> 06:49.349
THAT'S GREAT.

06:49.349 --> 06:50.517
YEAH.

06:50.517 --> 06:52.252
IT'S LIKE
I NEVER WENT AWAY.

06:52.252 --> 06:54.555
SO ARE YOU GUYS
SEEING EACH OTHER AGAIN?

06:54.555 --> 06:55.789
UH, NO, NO.

06:55.789 --> 06:58.859
HE'S NOT SEEING HER.
SHE JUST CAME BY THE HOUSE.

06:58.859 --> 07:01.802
I'M SEEING HER.

07:01.802 --> 07:04.204
LOOK AT YOU.

07:04.204 --> 07:06.607
SHE'S MAKING YOU
LIGHT UP AGAIN.

07:06.607 --> 07:07.908
NO PUN INTENDED.

07:07.908 --> 07:11.512
THAT'S NOT FUNNY,
WYATT.

07:11.512 --> 07:13.547
RELAX, JEFFREY.
I'M TALKING TO MY SISTER.

07:13.547 --> 07:14.715
I JUST THOUGHT
WE TALKED ABOUT ‐‐

07:14.715 --> 07:15.816
I KNOW WHAT YOU THOUGHT.

07:15.816 --> 07:18.018
I'VE HAD ENOUGH OF IT,
OKAY?

07:18.018 --> 07:19.753
NOW, I KNOW
YOU HAVE TO BE WITH ME.

07:19.753 --> 07:21.254
NOW CHILL!

07:27.761 --> 07:29.696
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
I'M SORRY.

07:29.696 --> 07:32.733
UM, I'M SORRY, AMANDA.
I'M JUST GONNA WAIT OUTSIDE.

07:32.733 --> 07:33.767
GOOD.

07:38.238 --> 07:40.206
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

07:40.206 --> 07:43.076
WOW. HE'S UPSET.

07:43.076 --> 07:45.612
OH,
HE'S DRIVING ME CRAZY.

07:45.612 --> 07:48.348
[ SOBS ]

07:54.087 --> 07:55.822
OH!

08:04.838 --> 08:07.407
[ SIGHS ]

08:14.748 --> 08:18.719
MAN,
THAT WAS A WHILE AGO.

08:18.719 --> 08:20.286
SO, HOW YOU BEEN?
I'VE BEEN GOOD.

08:20.286 --> 08:21.755
I CAME AS SOON AS I COULD,
MAN.

08:21.755 --> 08:22.923
THANK YOU.

08:22.923 --> 08:23.957
WHAT'S GOING ON?

08:23.957 --> 08:25.726
DO YOU KNOW
A BENNY YOUNG?

08:25.726 --> 08:28.328
YES, I DO.

08:28.328 --> 08:29.730
REALLY?

08:29.730 --> 08:30.997
YEAH.

08:30.997 --> 08:33.133
HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT?

08:33.133 --> 08:35.101
WELL, I WAS DOING
SOME RESEARCH ON HIM,

08:35.101 --> 08:36.870
AND I SAW YOUR NAME
AND DATE OF BIRTH

08:36.870 --> 08:38.004
ON HIS BIRTH CERTIFICATE.

08:38.004 --> 08:41.307
YEAH, HE'S MY SON.

08:41.307 --> 08:43.409
DAMN.

08:43.409 --> 08:46.580
WHAT? WHY ARE YOU DOING
RESEARCH ON HIM?

08:46.580 --> 08:49.249
[ SIGHS ]
HE'S IN TROUBLE.

08:49.249 --> 08:51.317
WHAT?
WHAT DID HE DO?

08:51.317 --> 08:53.019
HE WAS ARRESTED
FOR DRUG POSSESSION.

08:53.019 --> 08:55.355
NO.
I KNOW THAT KID.

08:55.355 --> 08:57.023
I'VE BEEN WATCHING HIM
FROM A DISTANCE.

08:57.023 --> 08:58.659
HE WOULDN'T DO THAT.
"FROM A DISTANCE"?

08:58.659 --> 09:01.001
I'M NOT IN HIS LIFE.

09:01.001 --> 09:02.503
WELL, I KNOW.

09:02.503 --> 09:04.738
I MEAN,
WE'VE BEEN FRIENDS SINCE IRAQ

09:04.738 --> 09:06.306
AND YOU NEVER MENTIONED
A SON.

09:06.306 --> 09:07.373
I KNOW, I KNOW.

09:07.373 --> 09:08.909
IT'S
A DIFFICULT SITUATION.

09:08.909 --> 09:10.611
HIS MOTHER AND I
ARE NOT CLOSE.

09:10.611 --> 09:12.979
THIS IS CRAZY.

09:12.979 --> 09:14.114
WHAT'S CRAZY?

09:14.114 --> 09:15.215
[ SIGHS ]

09:15.215 --> 09:16.817
I GOT TO
TELL YOU SOMETHING.

09:16.817 --> 09:17.818
OKAY.

09:17.818 --> 09:20.554
UH, I CAN'T LET THIS HAPPEN
TO YOU.

09:20.554 --> 09:22.455
WHAT, WHAT?

09:22.455 --> 09:24.224
LOOK, THIS IS BAD.

09:24.224 --> 09:25.826
IT'S REALLY BAD.

09:25.826 --> 09:27.828
WILL YOU JUST TELL ME
WHAT'S GOING ON?

09:27.828 --> 09:29.495
NO, I CAN'T TELL YOU,
NOT YET.

09:29.495 --> 09:31.865
BUT JUST KNOW
THAT HE'S BEING RAILROADED.

09:31.865 --> 09:33.333
BY WHO?

09:33.333 --> 09:36.236
IF I TELL YOU THAT,
THEY MAY COME AFTER ME.

09:36.236 --> 09:37.370
AFTER YOU?

09:37.370 --> 09:39.372
HOW FAR
DOES THIS THING GO UP?

09:39.372 --> 09:41.474
TO THE TOP OF THE BENCH.

09:41.474 --> 09:43.577
OKAY.

09:43.577 --> 09:44.811
WHAT CAN I DO?

09:44.811 --> 09:47.681
NOTHING...YET.

09:47.681 --> 09:50.083
I MAY BE FORCED
TO WORK SOMETHING OUT.

09:50.083 --> 09:52.586
BUT I'LL LET YOU KNOW.
JUST SIT TIGHT.

09:52.586 --> 09:54.420
AND IF ANYTHING HAPPENS
TO ME,

09:54.420 --> 09:57.924
KNOW ‐‐
KNOW THAT HE'S INNOCENT.

09:59.826 --> 10:03.436
LOOK, I GOT TO GO.
IT'S NOT THE BEST PLACE TO TALK.

10:03.436 --> 10:05.739
ALL RIGHT.
CAN WE MEET LATER?

10:05.739 --> 10:07.508
LOOK,
I'LL CALL YOU.

10:25.626 --> 10:27.093
[ KNOCK AT DOOR ]

10:27.093 --> 10:28.361
[ DOOR OPENS ]

10:28.361 --> 10:29.495
HEY, WYATT.

10:29.495 --> 10:31.364
WHAT?

10:31.364 --> 10:32.833
I, UM ‐‐
I HAVE SOME ERRANDS TO RUN,

10:32.833 --> 10:34.735
SO I'M JUST GONNA CALL WILL,
THE OTHER COUNSELOR,

10:34.735 --> 10:37.070
AND HE'LL JUST BE WITH YOU
FOR THE REST OF THE DAY, OKAY?

10:37.070 --> 10:40.240
GOOD. I GET A CHANCE
TO GET AWAY FROM YOU.

10:45.478 --> 10:46.479
[ SIGHS ] OKAY.

10:46.479 --> 10:48.048
UM, I'M SORRY.

10:48.048 --> 10:50.851
AMANDA, FEEL BETTER,

10:50.851 --> 10:52.418
AND I'LL JUST BE OUT HERE
UNTIL HE COMES.

10:52.418 --> 10:53.520
Amanda: THANKS.

10:53.520 --> 10:57.558
YOU DO THAT,
JEFFREY!

10:57.558 --> 11:00.493
[ GROANS ]

11:00.493 --> 11:01.568
HOW ARE YOU FEELING?

11:01.568 --> 11:02.803
[ SIGHS ]

11:02.803 --> 11:05.071
IT HURTS WHEN I MOVE.

11:05.071 --> 11:09.109
WELL,
YOU DON'T KNOW PAIN

11:09.109 --> 11:11.111
UNTIL YOU TRY
TO STAND UP STRAIGHT.

11:11.111 --> 11:15.015
I LOOK FORWARD TO IT.

11:17.884 --> 11:20.420
HOW ARE YOUR SPIRITS?

11:20.420 --> 11:24.858
I'M RELIEVED IT'S OVER.

11:24.858 --> 11:27.894
YES, IT IS.

11:30.931 --> 11:34.434
MS. CRYER,
I WANT TO ASK YOU SOMETHING.

11:34.434 --> 11:35.468
HMM?

11:35.468 --> 11:40.607
IF SOMETHING HAD HAPPENED,
GOOD OR BAD,

11:40.607 --> 11:48.048
WHILE YOU WERE AWAY RESTING,
WOULD YOU WANT ME TO TELL YOU?

11:48.048 --> 11:53.720
YES. OF COURSE.

11:53.720 --> 11:57.924
THEN I NEED TO TELL YOU
SOMETHING.

11:57.924 --> 12:01.802
WHAT IS IT, HANNA?

12:01.802 --> 12:06.673
IT'S ABOUT
YOUR DAUGHTER.

12:06.673 --> 12:08.742
WHAT ABOUT AMANDA?

12:14.414 --> 12:16.750
MS. CRYER, AMANDA TRIED
TO COMMIT SUICIDE.

12:16.750 --> 12:19.119
NO!
SHH!

12:19.119 --> 12:20.587
IS SHE OKAY?

12:20.587 --> 12:23.423
MM!
SHE'S FINE, SHE'S FINE.

12:23.423 --> 12:26.727
[ WHIMPERS ]

12:26.727 --> 12:28.962
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT'S WRONG WITH HER.

12:28.962 --> 12:30.764
I TOLD YOU
SHE WAS FRAGILE.

12:30.764 --> 12:34.134
SHE CANNOT HANDLE
ANYTHING.

12:34.134 --> 12:36.837
WHAT DID SHE DO?

12:36.837 --> 12:39.773
WELL, SHE TOOK
A WHOLE LOT OF PILLS.

12:39.773 --> 12:44.110
BUT THEY FOUND HER
IN TIME.

12:44.110 --> 12:49.015
I DON'T KNOW WHAT ELSE TO DO,
HANNA.

12:49.015 --> 12:51.552
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT'S WRONG WITH HER.

12:51.552 --> 12:56.857
WE HAVE GIVEN HER EVERYTHING ‐‐
EVERYTHING.

12:56.857 --> 13:01.902
HOW CAN THAT CHILD
BE IN SO MUCH PAIN

13:01.902 --> 13:04.470
THAT SHE WANTS TO DIE?

13:04.470 --> 13:09.442
YOUR HUSBAND AND YOUR SON
HAVE BEEN THERE WITH HER,

13:09.442 --> 13:11.645
BUT ‐‐
BUT WHAT?

13:11.645 --> 13:15.682
SHE'S HERE.

13:15.682 --> 13:18.819
[ SIGHS ]
SHE'S ON THIS FLOOR.

13:18.819 --> 13:21.688
GREAT, GREAT.
DO THEY KNOW I'M HERE?

13:21.688 --> 13:23.890
NO, I DON'T THINK SO.

13:23.890 --> 13:27.193
WELL,
I NEED TO GET OUT OF HERE.

13:27.193 --> 13:30.196
NO, NO. YOU CAN'T.

13:30.196 --> 13:32.032
SHE'S SUPPOSED TO
GO HOME TODAY.

13:32.032 --> 13:34.234
I DON'T CARE.
I NEED TO GET OUT OF HERE.

13:34.234 --> 13:36.803
THE DOCTOR SAYS
JUST A COUPLE MORE DAYS.

13:36.803 --> 13:38.104
CALL THE DOCTOR.

13:38.104 --> 13:40.073
TELL HIM
I WANT TO GO HOME.

13:40.073 --> 13:42.576
NO, MA'AM, I WILL NOT.

13:42.576 --> 13:46.412
NOW,
I'M GONNA GO RUN THESE ERRANDS,

13:46.412 --> 13:47.881
AND I'LL BE BACK.

13:47.881 --> 13:49.683
I'M GOING HOME, HANNA.

13:49.683 --> 13:51.217
CALL THE DOCTOR.

13:51.217 --> 13:53.920
TELL HIM
IT'S TIME TO LEAVE.

13:53.920 --> 13:56.489
NO, MA'AM.

13:56.489 --> 13:58.959
I'M GONNA GO NOW,
ALL RIGHT?

13:58.959 --> 14:00.601
YOU STAY HERE
AND TRY TO GET SOME REST.

14:00.601 --> 14:02.102
HANNA...

14:02.102 --> 14:04.270
ALL RIGHT NOW.

14:04.270 --> 14:07.508
I'LL BE BACK.

14:07.508 --> 14:08.775
BYE‐BYE.

14:08.775 --> 14:11.444
HANNA ‐‐
I'LL BE BACK.

14:22.589 --> 14:25.826
[ SOBBING ]

14:47.914 --> 14:50.316
[ KNOCK AT DOOR ]

14:50.316 --> 14:52.152
WHO IS IT?

14:52.152 --> 14:55.589
JEFFREY.

14:55.589 --> 14:57.791
[ SIGHS ]
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

14:57.791 --> 14:59.425
I WANT TO TALK TO YOU.

14:59.425 --> 15:02.235
IS THAT THING
WITH YOU?

15:02.235 --> 15:05.238
NO.

15:05.238 --> 15:08.308
OKAY.

15:10.911 --> 15:12.345
COME IN.

15:12.345 --> 15:14.114
THANK YOU.

15:14.114 --> 15:16.750
MM‐HMM.

15:16.750 --> 15:18.151
WHERE'S YOUR BOY?

15:18.151 --> 15:20.721
OH,
HE'S WITH ANOTHER COUNSELOR.

15:20.721 --> 15:23.557
REALLY?

15:23.557 --> 15:25.258
WHAT MADE HIM DO THAT?

15:25.258 --> 15:28.562
YEAH, I MEAN,
IT JUST WAS NECESSARY.

15:28.562 --> 15:32.032
AND ‐‐ AND I NEEDED
TO RUN A FEW ERRANDS.

15:32.032 --> 15:34.134
I'M ONE OF THEM?

15:34.134 --> 15:36.002
I JUST WANTED
TO COME BY

15:36.002 --> 15:39.005
AND JUST APOLOGIZE
FOR WYATT'S BEHAVIOR.

15:39.005 --> 15:40.974
AH.

15:40.974 --> 15:43.343
YOU DON'T NEED TO
DO THAT FOR HIM.

15:43.343 --> 15:45.846
WELL,
I‐I THINK I SHOULD.

15:45.846 --> 15:49.282
I MEAN, HE'S A GREAT GUY,
BUT HE'S GOT A LOT OF DEMONS.

15:49.282 --> 15:52.385
AND YOU'RE HIS EXORCIST?

15:52.385 --> 15:55.589
WELL, I'M JUST TRYING
TO HELP HIM FIND HIMSELF.

15:55.589 --> 15:57.390
FIND WHAT?

15:57.390 --> 15:58.491
I THINK
THERE'S A LOT OF,

15:58.491 --> 16:01.067
UM, THINGS THAT HE HASN'T
EXPLORED IN LIFE YET

16:01.067 --> 16:02.769
WHICH CAUSES HIM
GREAT PAIN.

16:02.769 --> 16:05.606
LIKE WHAT?

16:05.606 --> 16:06.707
I'M NOT AT LIBERTY
TO SAY.

16:06.707 --> 16:08.141
BUT IT DOESN'T MEAN
HE'S A BAD PERSON.

16:08.141 --> 16:09.810
HE'S JUST
BEEN THROUGH A LOT.

16:09.810 --> 16:13.113
JEFFREY,
YOU KNOW HE'S NOT GAY, RIGHT?

16:13.113 --> 16:15.381
I NEVER SAID HE WAS.

16:15.381 --> 16:17.150
BUT YOU'RE HOPING HE IS.

16:17.150 --> 16:19.753
WHY WOULD I
BE HOPING THAT?

16:19.753 --> 16:22.756
BECAUSE
YOU'RE IN LOVE WITH HIM.

16:22.756 --> 16:25.225
DON'T ‐‐ DON'T GET DEFENSIVE
ABOUT IT.

16:25.225 --> 16:28.128
CANDACE, YOU'RE REALLY OUT THERE
SOMETIMES.

16:28.128 --> 16:31.497
JEFFREY, I GREW UP
AROUND GAY BOYS MY WHOLE LIFE.

16:31.497 --> 16:34.434
I LOVE THE KIDS.

16:34.434 --> 16:35.802
NOW CAN WE STOP THIS?

16:35.802 --> 16:39.172
COME OUT THE CLOSET INTO
THE LIGHT AND LIVE YOUR LIFE.

16:39.172 --> 16:41.441
I'M NOT IN THE CLOSET.

16:41.441 --> 16:43.343
THEN WHAT ARE YOU?

16:43.343 --> 16:44.945
I'M STRAIGHT.

16:44.945 --> 16:47.480
STRAIGHT TO A MAN.

16:47.480 --> 16:49.750
YOU KNOW, CANDACE,
MAYBE YOU JUST DON'T TURN ME ON.

16:49.750 --> 16:51.017
OH, PLEASE.

16:51.017 --> 16:53.754
I CAN TURN ON
A DEAD MAN.

16:53.754 --> 16:55.722
I KNOW MEN, JEFFREY.

16:55.722 --> 16:57.457
I KNOW ALL TYPES.

16:57.457 --> 16:59.526
I KNOW THE WOMANIZER.

16:59.526 --> 17:03.203
I KNOW THE SHY TYPE
THAT IN PRIVATE, HE'S A FREAK.

17:03.203 --> 17:06.773
I KNOW THE C. E. O.
WHO'S ALL POWERFUL IN THE OFFICE

17:06.773 --> 17:11.111
BUT LOVES TO WEAR MY HEELS
IN THE BEDROOM.

17:11.111 --> 17:13.580
I ALSO KNOW THE JOCK

17:13.580 --> 17:17.984
WHO LIKES FOR ME
TO PLAY WITH MY TOYS WITH HIM.

17:17.984 --> 17:23.156
AND I ALSO KNOW THE GAY MAN
WHO PRETENDS TO BE STRAIGHT.

17:23.156 --> 17:25.491
DO YOU KNOW JUDGES?

17:25.491 --> 17:27.027
A FEW.

17:27.027 --> 17:28.461
'CAUSE WYATT
SEEMS TO THINK

17:28.461 --> 17:30.330
THAT YOU AND HIS FATHER
HAD AN AFFAIR.

17:30.330 --> 17:32.365
WELL, WYATT ALSO THINKS
THAT YOU'RE STRAIGHT,

17:32.365 --> 17:34.768
SO SHOWS WHAT HE KNOWS.
[ LAUGHS ]

17:34.768 --> 17:38.204
I AM, CANDACE.

17:38.204 --> 17:42.308
WHY ARE YOU HERE?

17:42.308 --> 17:45.345
I WANTED TO APOLOGIZE.

17:45.345 --> 17:49.516
YOU DID NOT DRIVE ALL THIS WAY
TO APOLOGIZE.

17:49.516 --> 17:51.151
NOW,
WHY ARE YOU HERE?

17:51.151 --> 17:54.254
THAT'S IT.

17:54.254 --> 17:58.992
I AM NOT ONE OF THOSE
RICH AIRHEADS WHO YOU TALK TO.

17:58.992 --> 18:01.935
I AM ONE OF THE REALEST PEOPLE
YOU WILL EVER MEET.

18:01.935 --> 18:04.137
I CAN FLOAT
IN BOTH CIRCLES.

18:04.137 --> 18:06.740
I AM SO GOOD

18:06.740 --> 18:10.343
THAT I KNOW WHEN I'M BEING FED
A LOAD OF BULL.

18:10.343 --> 18:12.345
NOW,
WHY ARE YOU HERE?

18:23.423 --> 18:25.025
WHAT'S THAT?

18:25.025 --> 18:26.693
IT'S $2,000.

18:26.693 --> 18:29.730
FOR?

18:29.730 --> 18:33.199
I WANTED TO PAY YOU TO ‐‐
TO BE WITH ME.

18:33.199 --> 18:35.802
YOU WANT TO
SLEEP WITH ME?

18:35.802 --> 18:37.738
NO.

18:37.738 --> 18:40.874
I WANTED YOU TO BE MY DATE
FOR JUST A FEW EVENTS.

18:40.874 --> 18:42.308
"EVENTS"?

18:42.308 --> 18:44.177
YEAH.
I NEED SOMEBODY BY MY SIDE.

18:44.177 --> 18:45.411
MY DAD AND MR. CRYER ‐‐

18:45.411 --> 18:46.813
THEY'RE RUNNING,
AND I HAVE TO SHOW UP ‐‐

18:46.813 --> 18:49.650
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
NO. STOP.

18:49.650 --> 18:51.151
WHAT?
WHAT'S SO FUNNY?

18:51.151 --> 18:55.689
A HANDSOME, SEXY,
STRAIGHT MAN LIKE YOURSELF

18:55.689 --> 19:01.735
CAN'T FIND A GIRL
TO STAND WITH HIM, HMM?

19:01.735 --> 19:04.838
PLEASE.

19:04.838 --> 19:07.073
WHOSE IDEA IS THIS?

19:07.073 --> 19:08.942
IT'S MINE.

19:08.942 --> 19:12.012
NO.
IT'S NOT THE TRUTH.

19:12.012 --> 19:15.516
YOU THINK YOU'RE SO SMART,
DON'T YOU, CANDACE?

19:15.516 --> 19:20.153
I THINK
IT'S YOUR MOTHER'S IDEA.

19:20.153 --> 19:22.188
AND WHY
DO YOU THINK THAT?

19:22.188 --> 19:23.524
I MET YOUR MOTHER.

19:27.293 --> 19:28.962
I'VE SEEN
HOW SHE LOOKS AT YOU,

19:28.962 --> 19:32.766
AND I'VE SEEN HOW YOU BECOME
A 5‐YEAR‐OLD

19:32.766 --> 19:34.968
EVERY TIME SHE'S AROUND.

19:34.968 --> 19:39.372
THIS IS MY IDEA.

19:39.372 --> 19:41.808
EITHER YOU WANT TO DO IT
OR NOT.

19:41.808 --> 19:43.810
THIS IS SAD.

19:43.810 --> 19:45.145
HOW SO?

19:45.145 --> 19:47.313
HOW ARE YOU
LIVING YOUR LIFE?

19:47.313 --> 19:49.282
YOU'VE GOT TO BE
MISERABLE.

19:49.282 --> 19:50.717
YOU'RE IN THE CLOSET,

19:50.717 --> 19:52.619
YOU'RE IN LOVE
WITH A STRAIGHT MAN,

19:52.619 --> 19:58.324
AND NOW YOU'RE TRYING
TO BUY AN IMAGE FOR YOUR MOTHER.

19:58.324 --> 20:01.902
I GENUINELY FEEL SORRY
FOR YOU.

20:04.705 --> 20:09.209
I DON'T NEED YOUR PITY,
CANDACE, AND I'M NOT GAY.

20:09.209 --> 20:11.745
I'M JUST NOT COMFORTABLE
WITH WOMEN.

20:11.745 --> 20:15.348
BECAUSE YOU'RE GAY.

20:18.418 --> 20:20.721
YOU KNOW WHAT?
NEVER MIND.

20:23.289 --> 20:25.425
I'LL DO IT.

20:28.128 --> 20:31.965
REALLY?

20:31.965 --> 20:36.236
MM‐HMM.

20:36.236 --> 20:38.438
BUT ON ONE CONDITION.

20:38.438 --> 20:41.975
AND WHAT WOULD THAT BE?

20:41.975 --> 20:44.177
YOU HAVE TO
HAVE SEX WITH ME.

20:44.177 --> 20:47.047
CANDACE ‐‐

20:47.047 --> 20:48.915
JUST ONCE.

20:48.915 --> 20:50.483
I'M NOT HAVING SEX
WITH YOU.

20:50.483 --> 20:53.353
WHY? YOU PAID ME.

20:53.353 --> 20:55.856
THAT'S NOT
WHAT THIS IS ABOUT.

20:55.856 --> 20:58.158
WHAT ARE YOU SO AFRAID OF?

20:58.158 --> 21:01.067
I'M NOT SLEEPING
WITH YOU.

21:01.067 --> 21:02.636
I AIN'T TALKING
ABOUT THAT.

21:02.636 --> 21:04.538
I KNEW
YOU WOULDN'T SLEEP WITH ME.

21:04.538 --> 21:07.974
WHY ARE YOU SO AFRAID
TO COME OUT?

21:11.645 --> 21:13.113
I'M NOT GAY, CANDACE.

21:13.113 --> 21:16.182
CAN YOU PLEASE
STOP REPEATING YOURSELF?

21:16.182 --> 21:19.586
JEFFREY, DO YOU THINK
IF YOU SAY IT ENOUGH,

21:19.586 --> 21:22.589
THE FEELINGS
WILL GO AWAY?

21:22.589 --> 21:25.358
THEY WON'T.

21:25.358 --> 21:27.293
THAT'S WHO YOU ARE.

21:30.396 --> 21:31.865
FORGET I ASKED YOU.

21:36.369 --> 21:37.838
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

21:37.838 --> 21:40.641
THE TRUTH IS THE TRUTH.

22:15.849 --> 22:18.118
OH!

22:27.628 --> 22:30.430
Celine: HI.
HI.

22:30.430 --> 22:34.901
LONG DAY?

22:34.901 --> 22:36.970
YES,
IT WAS A VERY LONG DAY.

22:36.970 --> 22:39.039
I HEARD ABOUT AMANDA.

22:39.039 --> 22:40.306
IS IT TRUE?

22:40.306 --> 22:43.710
YEAH.

22:43.710 --> 22:45.979
SHE'S GONNA BE OKAY,
I HOPE?

22:45.979 --> 22:50.584
I'M, UH ‐‐ I'M GONNA PICK HER UP
AT THE HOSPITAL SOON.

22:50.584 --> 22:54.287
SHE'LL BE OKAY.

22:54.287 --> 22:55.689
HERE.

23:00.500 --> 23:03.169
THANK YOU.

23:06.807 --> 23:08.441
YOU LOOK TENSE.

23:08.441 --> 23:11.311
YES, I AM.

23:11.311 --> 23:12.846
I AM TENSE.
I'M VERY TENSE.

23:12.846 --> 23:18.885
I COULD RUN A BATH
FOR YOU.

23:18.885 --> 23:21.955
NO, THANK YOU.

23:21.955 --> 23:23.489
I could join you.

23:23.489 --> 23:25.659
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

23:25.659 --> 23:29.796
NO. NO, THANK YOU.

23:29.796 --> 23:31.998
PLEASE.

23:39.339 --> 23:41.742
REALLY, JIM?

23:41.742 --> 23:44.878
YOU'RE NEVER GOING TO BE MINE
AGAIN?

23:44.878 --> 23:47.781
[ SIGHS, LAUGHS ]

23:47.781 --> 23:50.551
CELINE, I WAS NEVER YOURS
TO BEGIN WITH.

23:50.551 --> 23:51.685
OH?

23:51.685 --> 23:54.454
SO YOU LIED
ABOUT EVERYTHING?

23:54.454 --> 23:57.057
YOU KNOW,
I'M HAVING A ROUGH DAY.

23:57.057 --> 23:59.292
I DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR THIS.

23:59.292 --> 24:03.036
BUT I MISS
OUR TIME TOGETHER.

24:03.036 --> 24:06.439
THAT TIME IS IN THE PAST.
IT'S OVER.

24:06.439 --> 24:08.241
COME ON.

24:08.241 --> 24:09.475
LET ME HELP YOU
REMEMBER THE PAST.

24:09.475 --> 24:10.811
CELINE, STOP.

24:10.811 --> 24:14.180
WHY? WE USED TO HAVE SO MUCH FUN
WHEN KATHERYN WAS AWAY.

24:14.180 --> 24:15.882
YES, WE DID.

24:15.882 --> 24:17.784
I KNOW.
I REMEMBER THAT.

24:17.784 --> 24:20.353
BUT THAT WAS THEN,
AND THIS IS NOW,

24:20.353 --> 24:22.422
AND THIS IS NOT FUN.

24:25.458 --> 24:27.293
REALLY?

24:27.293 --> 24:30.631
REALLY.
THIS HAS TO STOP.

24:30.631 --> 24:33.199
[ LAUGHS ]

24:33.199 --> 24:40.273
OH, JIM, WHO IS IT?

24:40.273 --> 24:44.878
EXCUSE ME?

24:44.878 --> 24:47.648
DID I SPEAK SPANISH TO YOU
JUST NOW?

24:47.648 --> 24:48.949
WHO IS IT?
OH, NO ‐‐

24:48.949 --> 24:50.984
YOU'RE NOT THE KIND OF MAN
WHO'S GONNA GO WITHOUT,

24:50.984 --> 24:52.285
SO I KNOW
YOU HAVE SOMEONE.

24:52.285 --> 24:53.419
WHO IS IT?

24:53.419 --> 24:56.022
I'M NOT DISCUSSING THIS
WITH YOU.

24:56.022 --> 24:58.692
OH, YES, YOU ARE.
NO, NO, I'M NOT.

24:58.692 --> 24:59.693
I'M NOT.

24:59.693 --> 25:00.894
I'M NOT GONNA HAVE THIS,
JIM.

25:00.894 --> 25:02.803
YOU'RE NOT GONNA HAVE THIS?
NO!

25:02.803 --> 25:04.204
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?

25:04.204 --> 25:05.506
YOU'RE NOT MY WIFE.

25:05.506 --> 25:07.473
YOU'RE
NOT GONNA HAVE THIS?

25:07.473 --> 25:12.646
NO. OH, GOD, NO,
I'M NOT YOUR WIFE.

25:12.646 --> 25:15.649
BUT YOU'RE NOT SLEEPING
WITH KATHERYN, SO WHO IS IT?

25:15.649 --> 25:16.883
OH, CELINE, STOP IT.

25:16.883 --> 25:19.285
STOP IT.
IT'S GOT TO BE SOMEONE.

25:19.285 --> 25:20.353
THIS IS OVER.

25:20.353 --> 25:22.523
OVER?

25:22.523 --> 25:23.590
NO, NO, NO.

25:23.590 --> 25:24.958
THIS CONVERSATION
IS NOT OVER.

25:24.958 --> 25:27.260
I'M NOT TALKING ABOUT
THIS CONVERSATION.

25:27.260 --> 25:29.395
I'M TALKING ABOUT THIS ‐‐
YOU, ME, US.

25:29.395 --> 25:31.497
IT'S OVER,
FINISHED, DONE.

25:31.497 --> 25:32.999
DID I SPEAK SPANISH?

25:32.999 --> 25:36.336
OH.

25:36.336 --> 25:38.905
[ GROANS ] SO WAIT.

25:38.905 --> 25:42.108
YOU DON'T LOVE ME
ANYMORE?

25:42.108 --> 25:45.111
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
HOW LAUGHABLE THAT IS?

25:45.111 --> 25:46.446
I NEVER LOVED YOU.

25:46.446 --> 25:49.149
WHAT?

25:49.149 --> 25:52.185
[ LAUGHS SARCASTICALLY ]
OKAY.

25:52.185 --> 25:54.087
YOU SAID YOU DID.

25:54.087 --> 25:57.090
I SAID I DID?
WELL, OF COURSE I SAID I DID.

25:57.090 --> 25:58.424
I WANTED
TO SLEEP WITH YOU.

25:58.424 --> 26:00.160
I SAID A LOT OF THINGS
I DIDN'T MEAN.

26:00.160 --> 26:02.235
I'M A GUY.

26:02.235 --> 26:04.304
FOR CRYING OUT LOUD,
ARE YOU THAT NAIVE?

26:04.304 --> 26:05.572
YOU BASTARD.

26:05.572 --> 26:08.108
YES, I'M A BASTARD,
AND YOU ARE THE BASTARD'S MAID.

26:08.108 --> 26:09.676
DON'T FORGET IT.

26:09.676 --> 26:11.211
OH, REALLY?
YES, REALLY?

26:11.211 --> 26:13.179
THAT'S ALL I AM TO YOU
IS A MAID?

26:13.179 --> 26:15.448
YES,
THAT'S ALL YOU ARE TO ME ‐‐

26:15.448 --> 26:17.818
UNLESS, OF COURSE,
YOU HAVE THE GOOD SENSE TO QUIT.

26:17.818 --> 26:18.919
NO.

26:18.919 --> 26:21.688
I'M NOT GONNA
MAKE IT THAT EASY.

26:21.688 --> 26:23.524
I AM NOT QUITTING.

26:23.524 --> 26:25.491
OKAY, THEN FINE.

26:25.491 --> 26:28.194
DO YOUR JOB,
STOP TRYING TO SEDUCE ME,

26:28.194 --> 26:29.730
BECAUSE IT'S PATHETIC.

26:35.401 --> 26:39.506
<i>TE ODIO.</i>

26:42.175 --> 26:45.646
LOOK THAT UP,
JIM CRYER.

27:00.527 --> 27:03.069
[ KNOCKING AT DOOR ]

27:05.338 --> 27:06.339
[ KNOCKING CONTINUES ]

27:06.339 --> 27:08.474
COMING.

27:12.012 --> 27:13.514
HANNA.

27:13.514 --> 27:14.715
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

27:14.715 --> 27:16.282
I'VE BEEN TRYING
TO CALL YOU.

27:16.282 --> 27:18.318
WELL, I'VE BEEN BUSY,
LIKE I AM NOW.

27:18.318 --> 27:20.086
WELL,
I NEEDED TO TALK TO YOU.

27:20.086 --> 27:22.122
WELL, I TOLD YOU I DON'T HAVE
ANYTHING TO SAY TO YOU.

27:22.122 --> 27:24.057
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME
BENNY WAS IN JAIL?

27:24.057 --> 27:26.226
EXCUSE ME?

27:26.226 --> 27:28.862
WHEN HAVE YOU EVER CARED
WHAT HAPPENED TO BENNY?

27:28.862 --> 27:30.831
I TOLD YOU I WANTED TO BE
PART OF HIS LIFE.

27:30.831 --> 27:32.699
WELL, YOU SHOULD HAVE
THOUGHT ABOUT THAT

27:32.699 --> 27:34.568
20‐SOMETHING YEARS AGO,
WHEN HE REALLY NEEDED YOU.

27:34.568 --> 27:37.103
WELL, HE NEEDS ME NOW.

27:37.103 --> 27:38.338
NOT LIKE HE DID

27:38.338 --> 27:40.974
WHEN I WAS TRYING TO TEACH HIM
HOW TO TIE A TIE

27:40.974 --> 27:44.678
OR THE FIRST TIME HE GOT BEAT UP
ON THE PLAYGROUND,

27:44.678 --> 27:46.513
NOR THE TIME
I WAS TRYING TO TEACH HIM

27:46.513 --> 27:49.215
THE VALUE OF BEING A MAN.

27:49.215 --> 27:50.851
I DIDN'T COME HERE
TO FIGHT WITH YOU.

27:50.851 --> 27:52.619
I SEE YOU'RE UPSET.
NO, NO, NO. UNH‐UNH.

27:52.619 --> 27:54.287
YOU'RE NOT
COMING IN HERE.

27:54.287 --> 27:55.789
AND YOU'RE DAMN RIGHT
I'M UPSET.

27:55.789 --> 27:58.024
YOU WANT TO COME IN HERE NOW,
AFTER ALL THESE YEARS,

27:58.024 --> 27:59.626
AFTER I DONE RAISED HIM?

27:59.626 --> 28:01.467
I'M TRYING TO ‐‐

28:01.467 --> 28:02.836
TRYING TO WHAT?

28:02.836 --> 28:05.572
TRYING TO HELP.

28:05.572 --> 28:07.708
I DON'T NEED YOUR HELP.

28:07.708 --> 28:10.310
I DIDN'T NEED IT THEN,
AND I SURE DON'T NEED IT NOW.

28:10.310 --> 28:12.145
OKAY.
THAT'S MIGHTY CHRISTIAN OF YOU.

28:12.145 --> 28:15.649
OH, ARE YOU REALLY GONNA
PLAY THAT CARD WITH ME, TONY?

28:15.649 --> 28:18.318
NO. I'M JUST SAYING THAT
WE'RE TAUGHT TO FORGIVE, RIGHT?

28:18.318 --> 28:19.485
AND I HAVE FORGIVEN YOU,

28:19.485 --> 28:21.087
BUT THAT DON'T MEAN
I GOT TO TOLERATE YOU.

28:21.087 --> 28:22.355
NOW
WOULD YOU PLEASE LEAVE?

28:22.355 --> 28:25.959
I KNOW WHY HE'S IN JAIL.

28:25.959 --> 28:27.594
WHAT?

28:27.594 --> 28:28.995
LET ME HELP HIM.

28:28.995 --> 28:30.664
WHAT CAN YOU DO
THAT I CAN'T?

28:30.664 --> 28:32.498
SEE,
I'VE ALREADY PROVEN I COULD.

28:32.498 --> 28:34.334
I KNOW PEOPLE DOWNTOWN.

28:34.334 --> 28:36.302
I KNOW DOWNTOWN, TOO.
PLEASE.

28:36.302 --> 28:40.140
HE WAS SET UP.

28:40.140 --> 28:43.343
WHAT?

28:43.343 --> 28:46.346
WHAT DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT THAT?

28:46.346 --> 28:48.248
I HAVE A FRIEND
WHO'S A DETECTIVE,

28:48.248 --> 28:50.651
AND HE WAS TELLING ME
THAT HE KNOWS WHAT HAPPENED.

28:50.651 --> 28:53.554
COME ON IN.

28:56.923 --> 28:58.324
TELL ME.

28:58.324 --> 29:01.027
HE ‐‐ HE HASN'T TOLD ME
EVERYTHING,

29:01.027 --> 29:04.370
BUT WE'RE SUPPOSED TO MEET LATER
TO GET ALL THE DETAILS.

29:04.370 --> 29:07.040
DON'T PLAY WITH ME,
TONY.

29:07.040 --> 29:08.742
YOU REALLY THINK
YOU CAN HELP HIM?

29:08.742 --> 29:11.778
YES.
I CAN, AND I WILL.

29:11.778 --> 29:13.580
AS SOON AS I GET
ALL THE INFORMATION,

29:13.580 --> 29:16.617
I WILL CALL YOU, OKAY?

29:16.617 --> 29:17.984
OKAY.

29:19.920 --> 29:23.123
LISTEN, I DON'T GET GOOD
CELL RECEPTION IN THE HOSPITAL,

29:23.123 --> 29:24.658
SO YOU JUST TEXT ME,

29:24.658 --> 29:26.827
AND THEN I'LL STEP OUT
AND CALL YOU BACK.

29:26.827 --> 29:28.529
IN THE HOSPITAL?
ARE YOU OKAY?

29:28.529 --> 29:29.596
OH, PLEASE.

29:29.596 --> 29:32.232
JUST ANOTHER PART OF MY LIFE
YOU MISSED.

29:32.232 --> 29:34.200
I'M FINE.

29:34.200 --> 29:36.937
I HAVE A FRIEND THERE.

29:36.937 --> 29:38.438
CAN I TAKE YOU
OVER THERE?

29:38.438 --> 29:40.907
NO.
I WILL CATCH THE BUS,

29:40.907 --> 29:42.408
AS I HAVE BEEN DOING
ALL THESE YEARS.

29:42.408 --> 29:43.544
IT LOOKS LIKE RAIN.

29:43.544 --> 29:45.612
WELL, I HAVE A RAINCOAT,
THANK YOU.

29:45.612 --> 29:46.747
EXCUSE ME.

29:46.747 --> 29:48.281
[ CHUCKLES ] OKAY, FINE.

29:48.281 --> 29:50.884
YOU ARE STILL
AS STUBBORN AS EVER.

29:50.884 --> 29:52.686
YES, I AM.

29:52.686 --> 29:55.689
I WANT TO SEE HIM.

29:55.689 --> 29:57.558
WHAT?
BENNY, IN JAIL.

29:57.558 --> 29:59.192
I'M GONNA GO SEE HIM.

29:59.192 --> 30:01.868
THE DETECTIVE
IS GONNA GET ME IN.

30:01.868 --> 30:03.303
SEE HIM FOR WHAT?

30:03.303 --> 30:07.307
I THINK IT'S ABOUT TIME
HE KNOWS WHO HIS FATHER IS.

30:07.307 --> 30:09.710
[ SCOFFS ]

30:09.710 --> 30:11.578
YOU WANT TO SEE HIM NOW,

30:11.578 --> 30:15.015
AT THIS MOMENT,
WHEN HE'S LOCKED UP?

30:15.015 --> 30:17.584
OH,
THAT'S REAL SMART, TONY.

30:17.584 --> 30:18.585
[ CHUCKLES ]

30:18.585 --> 30:21.187
YOU'VE ALWAYS BEEN BAD
WITH TIMING,

30:21.187 --> 30:22.723
BUT THIS IS A BIT MUCH.

30:22.723 --> 30:25.025
THIS IS THE WORST
I'VE EVER SEEN.

30:25.025 --> 30:26.727
HE NEEDS ME.

30:26.727 --> 30:28.829
HE DOESN'T EVEN KNOW
YOU EXIST.

30:28.829 --> 30:30.764
WELL,
IT'S ABOUT TIME HE DOES.

30:30.764 --> 30:35.168
DON'T GO NEAR MY CHILD
WITH THIS FOOLISHNESS, TONY.

30:35.168 --> 30:36.537
FOOLISHNESS?
I'M HIS FATHER!

30:36.537 --> 30:40.674
TONY ‐‐
I NEED TO BE THERE!

30:40.674 --> 30:43.376
SEE, YOU DIDN'T WANT TO HAVE
NO RELATIONSHIP WITH ME,

30:43.376 --> 30:44.377
AND THAT WAS FINE.

30:44.377 --> 30:47.313
I FORGAVE YOU
FOR THAT THEN.

30:47.313 --> 30:48.915
BUT YOU WILL NOT DESTROY

30:48.915 --> 30:54.721
THE ONLY RELATIONSHIP THAT
MEANS SOMETHING TO ME, NOT NOW.

30:54.721 --> 30:57.924
DON'T DO THIS, TONY.

30:57.924 --> 31:01.735
YOU STAY AWAY
FROM MY CHILD.

31:01.735 --> 31:04.738
NOW, YOU CAN DO WHAT YOU CAN
TO HELP HIM,

31:04.738 --> 31:09.510
BUT YOU STAY AWAY
FROM MY CHILD.

31:26.593 --> 31:28.161
HI.

31:28.161 --> 31:30.330
HI.

31:38.772 --> 31:40.273
HOW ARE YOU?

31:40.273 --> 31:43.109
I'M FINE.

31:43.109 --> 31:46.112
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

31:46.112 --> 31:49.349
YES, I AM.

31:49.349 --> 31:53.419
OKAY.

31:53.419 --> 31:57.290
YOU LOOK NICE.

31:57.290 --> 32:00.794
THANK YOU.

32:00.794 --> 32:03.537
WHO BROUGHT YOU
THE FLOWERS?

32:03.537 --> 32:06.172
WYATT AND JEFFREY.

32:06.172 --> 32:08.975
THEY'RE BEAUTIFUL.
YEAH.

32:13.246 --> 32:16.983
LOOK, AMANDA, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO SAY TO YOU.

32:16.983 --> 32:18.351
I'VE NEVER
BEEN AROUND ANYONE

32:18.351 --> 32:19.986
WHO TRIED TO TAKE THEIR LIFE
BEFORE.

32:19.986 --> 32:24.357
I'VE SEEN PEOPLE
TAKE OTHER PEOPLE'S LIVES,

32:24.357 --> 32:25.959
BUT NEVER THIS.

32:25.959 --> 32:28.061
I KNOW YOU HAVE.

32:28.061 --> 32:30.697
YEAH. WHERE I'M FROM,
THAT'S COMMON.

32:30.697 --> 32:32.766
BUT LIFE
IS WHAT YOU MAKE IT.

32:32.766 --> 32:33.767
[ SIGHS ]

32:33.767 --> 32:34.868
YOU CAN'T GIVE UP

32:34.868 --> 32:36.970
EVERY TIME YOU GET HURT
OR YOU FEEL BAD OR ‐‐

32:36.970 --> 32:39.740
OR RAPED.

32:42.008 --> 32:46.346
I KNOW WHAT HE DID TO YOU,
AND I'M SO SORRY.

32:46.346 --> 32:48.915
YOU TOLD ME
TO GO FLIRT WITH HIM.

32:48.915 --> 32:52.185
I DIDN'T KNOW
HE WOULD DO THAT TO YOU.

32:52.185 --> 32:56.990
HE HURT ME.

32:59.726 --> 33:01.568
I KNOW.

33:01.568 --> 33:05.639
I'VE BEEN HURT BEFORE,
TOO.

33:08.809 --> 33:10.343
WERE YOU RAPED?

33:10.343 --> 33:13.547
YES.

33:13.547 --> 33:16.182
WERE YOU A VIRGIN?

33:16.182 --> 33:19.853
YES.

33:19.853 --> 33:23.590
I WAS A VIRGIN,
CANDACE.

33:23.590 --> 33:24.925
YOU WERE?

33:24.925 --> 33:27.861
YEAH.

33:27.861 --> 33:31.598
AMANDA...
WHAT?

33:31.598 --> 33:33.934
...IF YOU WERE A VIRGIN,

33:33.934 --> 33:36.436
WHY DID YOU HAVE
A PREGNANCY TEST?

33:36.436 --> 33:37.470
WHAT?

33:37.470 --> 33:39.540
THE PREGNANCY TEST
IN THE BATHROOM.

33:39.540 --> 33:40.807
I SAW IT ON THE FLOOR.

33:40.807 --> 33:44.645
THAT WAS YOURS, RIGHT?

33:44.645 --> 33:47.413
YEAH.

33:47.413 --> 33:49.282
WHY DID YOU HAVE IT?

33:49.282 --> 33:56.022
'CAUSE I WANTED TO SEE
IF HE MADE ME PREGNANT.

33:56.022 --> 33:58.792
AND HE DID.

33:58.792 --> 34:01.301
[ SCOFFS ]

34:01.301 --> 34:03.269
HOW ‐‐
HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT?

34:03.269 --> 34:05.806
I KNOW.

34:05.806 --> 34:08.575
I FEEL IT
GROWING INSIDE OF ME.

34:08.575 --> 34:11.011
I'M PREGNANT.

34:11.011 --> 34:12.345
WHAT?

34:12.345 --> 34:17.851
I'M PREGNANT.

34:17.851 --> 34:20.721
AMANDA,
YOU ARE NOT PREGNANT.

34:20.721 --> 34:24.290
YES, I AM.

34:24.290 --> 34:28.328
IF THE PROFESSOR WAS
THE ONLY MAN YOU'VE SLEPT WITH,

34:28.328 --> 34:31.497
AND THAT WAS ONLY
A FEW DAYS AGO,

34:31.497 --> 34:33.433
WHY WOULD YOU THINK THAT?

34:33.433 --> 34:34.968
IT SAID IT WAS POSITIVE.

34:34.968 --> 34:36.503
I KNOW. I SAW THAT.

34:36.503 --> 34:38.371
BUT THAT'S NOT POSSIBLE.

34:38.371 --> 34:43.443
I SAW THE TEST, CANDACE.

34:43.443 --> 34:47.681
AMANDA,
THAT COULD NOT HAVE HAPPENED.

34:47.681 --> 34:51.051
SO YOU'RE SAYING I'M TOO DUMB
TO READ A PREGNANCY TEST?

34:51.051 --> 34:53.219
I SAW IT.
IT WAS POSITIVE, CANDACE.

34:53.219 --> 34:55.956
AMANDA, RELAX, PLEASE.

34:55.956 --> 34:57.658
I SAW IT.
IT WAS POSITIVE.

34:57.658 --> 35:01.902
BUT IT'S OBVIOUSLY
A FALSE POSITIVE, OKAY?

35:01.902 --> 35:04.805
YOU CAN'T GET PREGNANT
THAT QUICKLY.

35:04.805 --> 35:08.108
YEAH, WELL,
I HOPE YOU'RE RIGHT.

35:08.108 --> 35:10.276
I KNOW I AM.

35:13.514 --> 35:19.419
NOW...
HE CAN'T GET AWAY WITH THIS.

35:19.419 --> 35:22.355
HE IS
THE LOWEST OF THE LOW.

35:22.355 --> 35:24.290
YOU HAVE TO TELL YOUR FATHER
WHAT HAPPENED.

35:24.290 --> 35:26.593
NO. I CAN'T DO THAT.

35:26.593 --> 35:28.028
YES, YOU HAVE TO.

35:28.028 --> 35:30.731
NO ONE
CAN KNOW ABOUT THIS.

35:30.731 --> 35:32.699
I DON'T WANT YOU
TO TELL ANYONE.

35:32.699 --> 35:35.501
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

35:35.501 --> 35:37.270
I CAN'T DO IT.

35:37.270 --> 35:40.440
AMANDA,
YOU DON'T HAVE TO.

35:40.440 --> 35:42.208
AND DON'T TELL HIM.

35:42.208 --> 35:44.177
DON'T YOU SAY A WORD.

35:44.177 --> 35:45.879
DON'T.

35:45.879 --> 35:48.615
I WON'T, I WON'T.

35:48.615 --> 35:52.719
I'M SORRY.
I CAN'T DO THIS.

35:52.719 --> 35:56.823
YOU DON'T HAVE
ANYTHING TO APOLOGIZE ABOUT.

35:59.425 --> 36:00.861
YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.

36:00.861 --> 36:05.471
THANKS FOR BEING MY FRIEND,
CANDACE.

36:05.471 --> 36:08.809
SURE, AMANDA.

36:19.452 --> 36:20.887
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

36:26.993 --> 36:28.995
HI.
HI.

36:28.995 --> 36:31.965
JEFFREY,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

36:31.965 --> 36:35.501
UM...LISTEN, UH,
WE NEED TO TALK.

36:35.501 --> 36:38.371
YEAH, SURE.
COME ON IN.

36:38.371 --> 36:39.706
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

36:42.108 --> 36:43.777
THANK YOU.

36:43.777 --> 36:47.347
WHAT'S UP?
WHAT'S GOING ON?

36:47.347 --> 36:48.749
YOU KNOW THAT
I'VE BEEN WORKING WITH WYATT

36:48.749 --> 36:49.783
FOR A LONG TIME,
RIGHT?

36:49.783 --> 36:52.786
YES. AND YOU'RE DOING
SUCH AN AMAZING JOB.

36:52.786 --> 36:54.755
HE SEEMS SO MUCH BETTER.

36:54.755 --> 36:58.224
HE IS. AND THAT'S WHY
I WANTED TO TALK TO YOU.

36:58.224 --> 36:59.526
OKAY.

36:59.526 --> 37:02.569
IT'S VERY IMPORTANT TO ME
THAT HE DOESN'T RELAPSE.

37:02.569 --> 37:03.637
OF COURSE.

37:03.637 --> 37:07.440
AND I THINK THAT HE WILL
WITH YOU AROUND.

37:07.440 --> 37:10.443
UH, WHAT?
[ CHUCKLES ]

37:10.443 --> 37:12.879
YES.

37:12.879 --> 37:15.348
BUT I‐I WOULD NEVER DO ANYTHING
TO MAKE HIM RELAPSE.

37:15.348 --> 37:17.551
NO, NO, NO, NO.
IT'S NOT EVEN THAT.

37:17.551 --> 37:20.621
IT'S JUST THAT
HE CAN GET LOST IN PEOPLE

37:20.621 --> 37:22.422
AND SITUATIONS AND THEN,

37:22.422 --> 37:25.358
WHEN THINGS DON'T GO THE WAY
THAT HE WANTS THEM TO GO,

37:25.358 --> 37:26.492
HE CAN RELAPSE.

37:26.492 --> 37:28.662
NOW,
I JUST DON'T THINK

37:28.662 --> 37:33.700
THAT HE'S STRONG ENOUGH
TO BE IN A RELATIONSHIP YET.

37:33.700 --> 37:36.069
UH...I SEE.

37:36.069 --> 37:37.137
NOW,
DON'T GET ME WRONG.

37:37.137 --> 37:38.539
I THINK
THE TWO OF YOU SHOULD DATE.

37:38.539 --> 37:42.008
BUT JUST NOT NOW.

37:42.008 --> 37:43.176
IT'S TOO SOON.

37:43.176 --> 37:46.412
OKAY.

37:46.412 --> 37:49.850
UM, YEAH. I UNDERSTAND.

37:49.850 --> 37:53.086
YEAH?
I KNOW THIS IS HARD.

37:53.086 --> 37:59.476
IT IS
BECAUSE I‐I LOVE HIM SO MUCH.

38:00.694 --> 38:05.105
WELL, IF YOU REALLY LOVE HIM,
THEN LET HIM GO.

38:05.105 --> 38:09.075
AND ‐‐ AND DO YOU THINK THAT
THAT'S BEST?

38:09.075 --> 38:12.345
YES.

38:12.345 --> 38:14.581
BUT YOU CAN'T
BREATHE A WORD OF THIS TO HIM.

38:14.581 --> 38:17.450
[ SNIFFLES ]

38:17.450 --> 38:22.422
UH...YEAH, I‐I WON'T.

38:22.422 --> 38:24.658
WE WERE ACTUALLY SUPPOSED TO
MEET TONIGHT

38:24.658 --> 38:26.827
AT HIS PARENT'S HOUSE
FOR DINNER, SO ‐‐

38:26.827 --> 38:27.928
YEAH?

38:27.928 --> 38:30.063
WHICH ‐‐ YEAH,
WHAT SHOULD I TELL HIM?

38:30.063 --> 38:31.932
I'LL LET HIM KNOW
THAT YOU CAN'T MAKE IT.

38:31.932 --> 38:33.033
YOU WILL?

38:33.033 --> 38:35.736
YEAH. IT'S NO PROBLEM.

38:39.372 --> 38:41.307
OKAY. UM...

38:41.307 --> 38:43.644
YEAH?

38:43.644 --> 38:46.212
I'M SORRY.

38:46.212 --> 38:48.582
BUT THIS ISN'T FOREVER.

38:48.582 --> 38:50.617
JUST GIVE ME A YEAR.

38:50.617 --> 38:52.986
A YEAR?
YES.

38:52.986 --> 38:56.056
AND IF HE STILL WANTS TO
BE WITH YOU AT THE END OF THAT,

38:56.056 --> 38:59.159
THEN I'M SURE HE'LL BE
STRONG ENOUGH TO HANDLE IT.

38:59.159 --> 39:01.835
A YEAR?

39:01.835 --> 39:06.540
AT LEAST.

39:06.540 --> 39:09.843
WOW. THAT'S ‐‐
THAT'S A REALLY LONG TIME.

39:09.843 --> 39:13.947
WELL,
THESE THINGS TAKE TIME.

39:13.947 --> 39:19.319
YEAH. I'LL BET.

39:19.319 --> 39:22.122
WELL, THANK YOU.

39:22.122 --> 39:26.993
AND, UM, PLEASE,
IGNORE HIS PHONE CALLS.

39:26.993 --> 39:32.733
I KNOW THIS WOULD BE HARD,
BUT, UH, IT'S FOR HIS OWN GOOD.

39:32.733 --> 39:34.935
SURE.

39:34.935 --> 39:37.170
YEAH?

39:37.170 --> 39:44.464
[ SNIFFLES ]
YEAH, SURE.

39:44.477 --> 39:48.281
GOOD.

39:50.784 --> 39:54.721
WELL, THIS IS THE DUMBEST THING
I HAVE EVER SEEN YOU DO.

39:54.721 --> 39:59.159
IT'S BECAUSE YOU HAVEN'T
KNOWN ME LONG ENOUGH.

39:59.159 --> 40:00.727
HERE.

40:00.727 --> 40:04.605
I AM NOT LEAVING
IN THAT WHEELCHAIR.

40:04.605 --> 40:06.306
MRS. CRYER, YOU HAVE TO.

40:06.306 --> 40:08.274
NO, I DON'T.

40:08.274 --> 40:10.443
MOVE IT!

40:17.350 --> 40:19.653
[ SIGHS ]

40:19.653 --> 40:21.354
I KNOW YOU'RE IN PAIN.

40:21.354 --> 40:24.758
[ Shakily ]
EVERY DAY OF MY LIFE.

40:24.758 --> 40:26.026
MRS. CRYER...

40:26.026 --> 40:29.663
IS THE COAST CLEAR?

40:29.663 --> 40:31.331
YOU SHOULDN'T
BE DOING THIS.

40:31.331 --> 40:33.099
[ SIGHS ]

40:33.099 --> 40:35.536
HANNA,
I WANT TO GO HOME.

40:35.536 --> 40:37.771
YOU'RE IN PAIN.

40:37.771 --> 40:40.741
AND WE HAVE MEDS FOR THAT.

40:40.741 --> 40:44.878
AND YOU WILL BE THERE TO HELP ME
KEEP MY DRESSINGS CLEAN.

40:44.878 --> 40:48.148
NOW STOP THIS FUSS
AND LET'S GO.

40:48.148 --> 40:49.983
[ SIGHS ]

40:49.983 --> 40:51.017
ARE THEY GONE?

40:51.017 --> 40:55.121
I DON'T KNOW.

40:55.121 --> 40:56.790
THEY SHOULD BE.

40:56.790 --> 40:59.092
ALL RIGHT.

40:59.092 --> 41:01.668
LET'S GO.

41:01.668 --> 41:03.604
OKAY.

41:08.141 --> 41:10.944
COME ON NOW.

41:10.944 --> 41:14.180
[ TV PLAYS INDISTINCTLY ]

41:22.388 --> 41:26.359
Jim: WHY DON'T WE GET SOME,
UH ‐‐ SOME ICE CREAM?

41:27.828 --> 41:29.495
JIM?

41:30.997 --> 41:32.533
KATHERYN?

41:32.533 --> 41:36.436
[ SIGHS ]

41:36.436 --> 41:38.739
Narrator: NEXT ON
"THE HAVES AND THE HAVE NOTS"...

41:38.739 --> 41:41.441
CANDACE DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING,
NOTHING AT ALL TO UPSET YOU?

41:41.441 --> 41:44.611
Jim: BUT WHAT SHE DOESN'T KNOW
IS THAT YOU'RE SO CALCULATING,

41:44.611 --> 41:46.880
THAT NO MOVE IS EVER MADE UNLESS
IT'S IN YOUR BEST INTERESTS,

41:46.880 --> 41:48.749
INCLUDING
YOUR FRIENDSHIP WITH HER.

41:48.749 --> 41:50.450
I HAVE A FRIEND.
HE TOLD ME YOU WERE INNOCENT.

41:50.450 --> 41:51.952
WHAT'S HIS NAME?
I CAN'T TELL YOU THAT.

41:51.952 --> 41:53.153
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
YOU CAN'T TELL ME?!

41:53.153 --> 41:54.254
I THOUGHT YOU SAID
YOU CAME HERE TO HELP ME!

41:54.254 --> 41:56.557
YOU JUST
CAN'T TRUST THEM.

41:56.557 --> 41:59.259
THEY ALL HAVE ULTERIOR MOTIVES.
BUT NOT ME.

41:59.259 --> 42:00.794
ARE YOU SURE YOUR HUSBAND'S
NOT GONNA COME IN HERE

42:00.794 --> 42:01.968
AND NOTICE THAT
YOU'RE IN HERE SICK?

42:01.968 --> 42:04.871
STOP WASTING MY TIME.
I HAVE A HAIR APPOINTMENT.

42:04.871 --> 42:06.673
YOU BETTER START
TALKING TO HER.
